	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Mar 16th 8:05 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>My first post...<br><br>Two questions:<br>The first one is obvious and that is where is the best place to advance my lvl 17 Druid to the coveted lvl 19?&nbsp;&nbsp;I've been fighting along valiantly in NK with some success although the Oasis seemed better for quick exp.  BTW I despise grouping at this point so I'm a solo snob...any advice?<br><br>Second question is this:  As my Druid is an 'only a mother could love this face' halfling my cha is way low compared to say a wood elf.  Any easy quests for a lvl 17 to do for cha items?  Also would a higher charisma number make my charm animal spell more useful?  Those darn Griffawns hate it when I charm them and I can't keep em charmed long enough to be useful to me.  Thanks in advance for the advice!  <br><br>BTW this is my first and only character...I don't see how y'all have time to play more than one!!  This one consumes ALL my playing time and I'd hate to cheat this little guy outta some exp!<br>&nbsp;<br>Choriocapillaris Bentlash<br>Humble 20th circle Druid of Xev<br>When in doubt, throw tracers<br></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
