<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=98494416639255></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f98494416639255><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=8&mid=98494416639255>RE: A couple Druid questions...leveling and charisma</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=8&mid=98494416639255#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=9764><span id=Scholar>Quiick</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>69 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sun, Mar 18th 2:36 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[4.36]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>&nbsp;&nbsp;   I used the charm spell at lvl 30 to charm griffauns and kill carrion spiders for the silk.  They can do it pretty fast but make sure you keep your pet targeted so you can recharm as soon as possible.  Other than that charm was too unreliable for me.<br>     I learned the "get up, run, and drop" rhythm method of kiting by doing beetles in NK.  They are slow enough to out run without SoW and good practice.<br>     EK is a good place at lvl 17.  You can pick things up and kite them around the shore where you won't be bothered.  Using only dots and snare takes longer but it is the most mana efficient at that lvl and the least resisted and you can easly kite yellows without getting touched.  I never did like fear kiting because you can't control the direction your mob is going.  They can get you into trouble.<br>     At lvl 22 I moved to Lake of Ill Omen and stayed there till 29.  Kite along the zone wall near the Mill and again yellows are no problem and the best loot.  When you get bored with this you can group and kill sarnaks at the fort.  After lvl 24 the mobs are mostly blue but your new spells will allow you to take them down even faster.  Exp there came very fast.  The zone is getting kinda crowded but tracking gives you a big advantage over other players who don't have it.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
