	   <tr><td colspan=2>As it has been said before, charms aren't really that great because they don't last long enough.&nbsp;&nbsp;It's not until you get better spells that give you a permanent pet until it's worth it but by then, you probably don't need a pet anyway.<br>As for soloing, I found lavastorm was great experience.  I hunted the summoned creatures there; fire imps, fire sprites, lava crawlers, and fire elementals until 19th.  Thanks to the spell Expulsed Summoned which does 90+ DD, it was easy to just snare, root, nuke, med, repeat.  I even had a few group trips into Najena when I grew bored of Lavastorm.  Warning... lavastorm will spoil you though.  The 90+ DD spells at 19th cost a lot more mana than Expulsed and take longer to cast.  Don't expect to solo much longer after lavastorm.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
