<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=98486730913587></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f98486730913587><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=8&mid=98486730913587>RE: A couple Druid questions...leveling and charisma</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=8&mid=98486730913587#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=28638><span id= >kaot</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>4 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sat, Mar 17th 5:15 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I'll tell ya a nice place to lvl at 17 is ek.&nbsp;&nbsp;This is your chance to really get some good use of that panic animal spell, forget charm as someone said not worth the hassle.  Head over by the gorge zone in ek.  Kill gorge hounds and those spiders, not crag.  Crag may put a hurtin on ya, they have some pretty potent poison.  Mem that panic animal spell just in case ya aggro another gorge hound or run outta mana you can just reverse kite them.  Reverse kite all of them if ya have a decent weapon that does enough dmg.  I carry friends over there all the time that are around that lvl and sit back and just cast panic animal on the critters and let them do the fighting.  The loot may suck but you will lvl quick.  I think you can start hunting those hounds at around 16, con yellow.  After that, around 19, head over to OOT and kill gargs on spec isle.  There you will make up for the loot and then some that you didn't make from killing gorge hounds and the like.  Those gargs will drop 2 eyes at a time sometimes, the eyes sell for around 8pp each TO MERCHANT.  I know you are thinking these have to be kind of a rare drop.  No not at all, every 2 or 3 kills they drop.  BTW, the exp is excellent too.  Word of warning though on spec island, stay away from the topmost part of the island.  From the name you can tell why.  Also one other suggestion when there, bind at a spot on another island.  Sometimes you will aggro extra gargoyles on ya, so ya may have to run around the outside of the island til you get far enough and then gate to that other island. DO NOT BIND on same island, I repeat DO NOT BIND on same island as critters.  You will figure it out soon. hehehe   O yea, you have to kill the skellies first walking around on that island before the gargs will spawn.  If you carry a friend or 2 over there you can have a good time and get good loot and good exp, and everyone will walk away happy.  <br><br>my 2cp<br><br>Kaot Fieldstorm 29dru - Bertox<br><br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
