	   <tr><td colspan=2>First of all the charms really arent that useful... I have found they can be fun if you are right next to you're target and can immediatly sic the pet on it.&nbsp;&nbsp;On the same note if you are in North Karana hunting various griffs charm a wolf and then kite the griff all over you will have a large pack of wolves which will aggro on the griff...they dont do much damage so you get the kill but they take the hits.<br><br>Oasis is a good place to hunt, but crowded on my servers, I spent quite a few levels in Highpass due to the great faction of Gnoll Scalp quest.  <br><br>As for a good tactic in fighting creatures...my personal favorite is to kite a yellow mob (preferably one that hits for low frequent damage) until I am low on mana, throw on the most recent damage shield, and let the critter kill itself on me.<br><br>Good luck and to all Good gaming,<br>Arclueng<br>14th Wood elf druid Tunare<br>24th Half elf druid Ayonae Ro<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
